%%{init: {'theme': 'base', 'themeVariables': { 'primaryColor': '#ffffff', 'primaryTextColor': '#000000', 'primaryBorderColor': '#000000', 'lineColor': '#000000', 'textColor': '#000000'}}}%%
sequenceDiagram
    participant Dev as Developer
    participant CLI as nexus CLI
    participant BE as Nexus Backend<br/>(FastAPI)
    participant DB as SQLite
    participant Chroma as ChromaDB
    participant Conf as Confluence
    participant LLM as Lumin8 / LLM

    rect rgb(220, 240, 255)
        Note over Dev,LLM: 1️⃣  STARTUP — Skill Detection & Health Check
        Dev->>CLI: nexus (start)
        CLI->>CLI: detect_active_skill()<br/>→ git remote, files, keywords<br/>→ score skills
        CLI->>BE: GET /v1/models
        BE-->>CLI: 200 {data: [{id: "nexus-agent"}]}
        Note over CLI: Backend is alive ✓
        CLI->>BE: GET /api/skills
        BE-->>CLI: [{name, description, keywords}, ...]
        CLI->>CLI: Cache skill → ~/.nexus/config<br/>Store _nexus_last_skill = "staking"
        CLI-->>Dev: ✓ Ready (skill: staking)
    end

    rect rgb(230, 255, 230)
        Note over Dev,LLM: 2️⃣  @SKILL MID-SESSION SWITCH (preproc_user_input)
        Dev->>CLI: "@payments fix the settlement bug"
        CLI->>CLI: check_for_skills(inp)<br/>→ extract ["payments"] from message
        CLI->>BE: GET /api/skills/payments
        alt skill exists
            BE-->>CLI: 200 {name, description, skill_content}
            CLI->>CLI: main_model._nexus_extra_headers["X-Nexus-Skill"] = "payments"
            CLI->>CLI: arch_model._nexus_extra_headers["X-Nexus-Skill"] = "payments"
            CLI->>CLI: update_skill_mapping(repo_root, "payments")<br/>→ cache to ~/.nexus/config
            CLI->>CLI: Strip @payments → "fix the settlement bug"
            CLI-->>Dev: Switched product context to: payments
        else skill not found
            BE-->>CLI: 404
            CLI-->>Dev: ⚠ Skill @payments not found
        end
    end

    rect rgb(220, 255, 230)
        Note over Dev,LLM: 3️⃣  CHAT FLOW — Architect Model (Plan)
        Dev->>CLI: "fix the delegation bug"
        CLI->>CLI: check_for_skills() → no @tags<br/>Build prompt + context

        Note over CLI: Request 1: ARCHITECT (planner)
        CLI->>BE: POST /v1/chat/completions<br/>X-Nexus-Skill: staking<br/>model: "openai/nexus-architect"<br/>messages[0]: aider system prompt

        BE->>BE: Extract X-Nexus-Skill header
        BE->>DB: SELECT * FROM overflow_issues<br/>WHERE skill="staking" AND resolved_at IS NOT NULL
        DB-->>BE: [resolved issues...]
        BE->>Chroma: query("fix delegation bug", where={skill: "staking"})
        Chroma-->>BE: top-3 similar past fixes

        BE->>BE: Load SKILLS.md (staking)
        BE->>Conf: Search for "delegation bug"
        Conf-->>BE: [relevant architecture docs]

        BE->>BE: Build RAG context block:
        Note over BE: messages[0] = aider system prompt (UNTOUCHED)<br/>messages[1] = RAG block:<br/>  • SKILLS.md content<br/>  • Confluence chunks<br/>  • Past fixes from AgentOverflow<br/>messages[2+] = user/assistant history

        BE->>LLM: POST /v1/completions<br/>augmented_messages
        LLM-->>BE: plan text (natural language, NO SEARCH/REPLACE)

        BE-->>CLI: SSE stream → plan text
        CLI->>CLI: Buffer response
        CLI-->>Dev: ARCHITECT PLAN:<br/>"1. Check validator.rs line 47<br/>2. Add delegation check<br/>3. Test with epoch transition..."
    end

    rect rgb(255, 245, 220)
        Note over Dev,LLM: 3️⃣  EDIT FLOW — Editor Model (Code)
        Note over CLI: Response 1 buffered. Now request 2: EDITOR (applier)
        CLI->>BE: POST /v1/chat/completions<br/>X-Nexus-Skill: staking<br/>model: "openai/nexus-agent" (editor)<br/>messages[0]: aider system prompt<br/>messages[1]: architect plan (in context)

        BE->>Chroma: query("fix delegation bug", where={skill: "staking"})
        Chroma-->>BE: [same top-3 fixes]
        BE->>BE: Inject RAG at messages[1]<br/>(include past fixes)
        BE->>LLM: POST /v1/completions
        LLM-->>BE: SEARCH/REPLACE blocks

        BE-->>CLI: SSE stream → SEARCH/REPLACE
        CLI->>CLI: Parse SEARCH/REPLACE blocks
        CLI->>CLI: Apply edits to validator.rs
        CLI-->>Dev: ✓ Files edited<br/>validator.rs ← changed
    end

    rect rgb(255, 230, 230)
        Note over Dev,LLM: 4️⃣  AGENTOVERFLOW — /solve (Submit Issue)
        Dev->>CLI: /solve "delegation fails<br/>after epoch transition"

        CLI->>CLI: Capture rich context (automatic — no /add required):
        Note over CLI: git_diff, dirty_files, recent_commits<br/>all_files (full codebase)<br/>chat_files (explicitly /add'd)<br/>ident_mentions, file_mentions<br/>lint_outcome, test_outcome<br/>recent_messages (last 6)

        CLI->>BE: POST /api/overflow/ingest<br/>X-Nexus-Skill: staking<br/>{description, git_diff, all_files, chat_files,<br/>ident_mentions, file_mentions, lint_outcome, ...}

        BE->>Chroma: embed(description+ident_mentions)<br/>→ cosine similarity search
        Chroma-->>BE: best_sim = 0.62 (below 0.87 threshold)

        BE->>BE: NOVEL query (sim < 0.65)<br/>→ call LLM with RAG context
        Note over BE: Rank all_files by relevance<br/>(chat_files 50×, mentions 10×)<br/>Inject KB hits + skill content

        BE->>LLM: LLM call with ranked context
        LLM-->>BE: "Check epoch boundary..."

        BE->>BE: confidence = 0.82 ≥ 0.72<br/>→ AUTO-PERSIST (no human approval)

        BE->>DB: INSERT overflow_issues<br/>(id=uuid, skill, description, suggestion,<br/>confidence=0.82, persisted=1,<br/>expires_at=now+6mo)
        DB-->>BE: inserted

        BE->>Chroma: upsert(id=uuid,<br/>doc="Issue: ...\nAnswer: ...",<br/>metadata={skill, expires_at})
        Chroma-->>BE: searchable immediately

        BE-->>CLI: 200 {status:"ok", issue_id:"uuid-123",<br/>suggestion:"Check epoch boundary...",<br/>cached:false, confidence_score:0.82, persisted:true}

        CLI->>CLI: Store _nexus_last_issue_id = "uuid-123"
        CLI-->>Dev: 🤖 Analyzed with LLM.<br/>📚 Solution saved to team knowledge base.<br/>💡 "Check epoch boundary..."<br/>Resolution will auto-record on /commit
    end

    rect rgb(230, 230, 255)
        Note over Dev,LLM: 5️⃣  AGENTOVERFLOW — /commit (Auto-Resolve)
        Dev->>CLI: /commit
        CLI->>CLI: Perform git commit
        Note over CLI: (commit message is ignored)

        CLI->>CLI: Automatic resolution trigger:
        CLI->>CLI: git show HEAD (capture committed diff)
        CLI->>CLI: _nexus_maybe_auto_resolve()

        CLI->>BE: POST /api/overflow/resolve<br/>{issue_id: "uuid-123",<br/>committed_diff: "diff --git a/validator.rs...",<br/>resolution: null}

        BE->>DB: SELECT * FROM overflow_issues<br/>WHERE id = "uuid-123"
        DB-->>BE: issue record

        BE->>LLM: Summarize diff via LLM:<br/>"Describe in 1-2 sentences<br/>what this fix does"
        Note over LLM: (Given: original issue + diff)
        LLM-->>BE: "Added epoch boundary check in<br/>_validate_delegation() before state transition"

        BE->>DB: UPDATE overflow_issues<br/>SET resolution = "Added epoch boundary...",<br/>committed_diff = "diff --git...",<br/>resolved_at = datetime('now')<br/>WHERE id = "uuid-123"
        DB-->>BE: updated

        BE->>Chroma: collection.upsert(<br/>id="uuid-123",<br/>document="Issue: delegation fails after epoch...<br/>Resolution: Added epoch boundary check...",<br/>metadata={skill: "staking", description: "...", resolution: "..."})<br/>)
        Chroma-->>BE: upserted

        BE-->>CLI: 200 {status: "resolved"}

        CLI->>CLI: Clear _nexus_last_issue_id = null
        CLI->>CLI: Clear _nexus_last_issue_description = null
        CLI->>CLI: Clear _nexus_last_solve_suggestion = null

        CLI-->>Dev: 📚 AgentOverflow: fix captured.<br/>Knowledge base updated.

        Note over Chroma: NOW searchable by future /solve<br/>queries with similar issues
    end

    rect rgb(255, 245, 250)
        Note over Dev,LLM: 6️⃣  (OPTIONAL) /solved with Explicit Note
        alt Developer wants to add a detailed note
            Dev->>CLI: /solved "Root cause: epoch callback<br/>was firing before validator state flush"

            CLI->>CLI: Get _nexus_last_issue_id (if set)

            CLI->>BE: POST /api/overflow/resolve<br/>{issue_id: "uuid-123",<br/>resolution: "Root cause: epoch callback...",<br/>committed_diff: null}

            BE->>DB: UPDATE overflow_issues<br/>SET resolution = "Root cause: epoch...",<br/>resolved_at = datetime('now')

            BE->>Chroma: collection.upsert(id, doc, metadata)
            Chroma-->>BE: upserted

            BE-->>CLI: 200
            CLI-->>Dev: ✅ Fix captured.<br/>(explicit note stored)
        end
    end

    rect rgb(250, 250, 250)
        Note over Dev,LLM: 7️⃣  FUTURE: Next Developer Hits Similar Issue
        Note over Dev,LLM: (Flow repeats for new developer)
        Developer2->>CLI: /solve "validation broken<br/>around epoch transition"

        CLI->>BE: POST /api/overflow/ingest

        BE->>Chroma: query("validation broken epoch",<br/>where={skill: "staking"})
        Chroma-->>BE: [{id: "uuid-123", score: 0.89}<br/>score > threshold]

        BE->>DB: SELECT description, resolution<br/>FROM overflow_issues<br/>WHERE id = "uuid-123"
        DB-->>BE: {description: "delegation fails...",<br/>resolution: "Added epoch boundary..."}

        BE->>BE: Build suggestion from past fix
        BE-->>CLI: 200 {issue_id: "uuid-456",<br/>suggestion: "Similar issue:<br/>Added epoch boundary check before state flush"}

        Note over CLI,Dev: ⚡ Developer immediately sees<br/>the exact fix that worked<br/>for the previous developer!<br/>NO extra effort required.
    end
